  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Shipping Operator (Tankers)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Oversee daily vessel operations for assigned MR tankers, including voyage planning, port operations, bunkering, and documentation.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with masters, agents, charterers, suppliers, and internal teams to ensure smooth execution of voyages.</p></li><li><p>Monitor vessel performance, schedules, and costs to ensure operational efficiency and contractual compliance.</p></li><li><p>Handle pre-fixture and post-fixture operational matters, including laytime calculations and demurrage/despatch tracking.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with safety, regulatory, and company operational standards.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with technical and HSQE teams on vessel issues, incidents, and maintenance-related matters.</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate operational records and reports.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in Maritime Studies, Nautical Science, or a related discipline.</p></li><li><p>Prior experience as a Shipping Operator / Vessel Operator handling <strong>MR tankers</strong> is essential.</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of tanker operations, charter party terms, and voyage execution.</p></li><li><p>Good communication and coordination skills with the ability to manage multiple vessels and stakeholders.</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented, proactive, and able to work in a fast-paced operational environment.</p></li></ul>",
